slides.title: Controversy Network: Freedom of Speech and Social Media in 2015
slides.text: This is the network of the actors that take part the controversy in 2015 (from Google.co.uk)

slides.title: Core elements
slides.text: The centre of the network is animated by different actors: UK government reports (e.g. report on Freedom of expression in China), newspapers (e.g.The Guardian), blogs (e.g. Mattbritland), NGOs and Associations (e.g.AfricanInternetRights.org). There is a variety of themes: hate speech, child protection, politics.

slides.title: More external actor I
slides.text: Some actors have many links but occupy a more detached position in the overall network.

slides.title: More external actor II
slides.text: Some actors have many links but occupy a more detached position in the overall network (website that publicises alternatives to global capitalism; radical, co-operative, not-for-profit, social and ethical organisations, groups and events with a political focus. Independent, self-funded and not-for-profit, and voluntarily run).

slides.title: More external actor III
slides.text: Platform for open discussions on EU policies/politics

slides.title: More external actor IV
slides.text: British newspaper. The network shows how the article has been mentioned/re-posted in other media environments (either Social Media like Twitter, or websites like Stoponlineabuse.org.uk)
